description:
Join Multilogin as a Middle WordPress and PHP Developer and be a crucial part of the UI team within our Engineering department. In this role, you'll be pivotal in maintaining and enhancing our WordPress platform, developing custom PHP solutions, and optimizing our checkout and billing processes. Your success will be measured by the stability, performance, and user experience of our web platform. This position offers the opportunity to hone your WordPress and PHP skills, while directly contributing to our operational efficiency and market expansion goals.

**Responsibilities:**



* Maintain the WordPress instance, including plugins, configuration, and website performance;


* Develop and maintain custom PHP pages and templates for WordPress, ensuring they meet business requirements and standards;


* Develop, maintain, and design the checkout process, forms, and workflow for integration with the Unibee billing system using React;


* Troubleshoot and resolve website issues, ensuring minimal downtime and optimal user experience;


* Collaborate with the design team to implement new features and functionalities;


* Stay updated with the latest industry trends and technologies to ensure our platform remains competitive.


**Requirements:**



* Proven experience with WordPress development, including custom themes and plugins;


* Strong proficiency in PHP and MySQL, with a solid understanding of front-end technologies such as HTML, CSS, and JavaScript;


* Experience with integrating third-party APIs and payment gateways;


* Experience with React-based frameworks;


* Familiarity with version control systems;


* Good understanding of website architecture and aesthetics;


* Strong problem-solving skills and ability to work independently.
